Certainly! Here's the equivalent script in C# that generates two integer columns, with the first column containing random integers between 1 through 20, and the second column containing random integers between 1 through 100:

```csharp
using System;

class Program
{
    static void Main(string[] args)
    {
        // Generate 10 random rows
        int rows = 10;

        // Generate and print the table
        Console.WriteLine("First Column\tSecond Column");
        Random random = new Random();
        for (int i = 0; i < rows; i++)
        {
            int firstColumn = random.Next(1, 21);
            int secondColumn = random.Next(1, 101);
            Console.WriteLine($"{firstColumn}\t\t{secondColumn}");
        }
    }
}
```

This C# code will also generate 10 rows of random integers in the desired ranges. Each time you run the code, it will produce different numbers. You can modify the `rows` variable to generate more or fewer rows as needed.

Certainly! To print the results in CSV format in C#, you can use the `StreamWriter` class to write the data to a file with a ".csv" extension. Here's an updated version of the code:

```csharp
using System;
using System.IO;

class Program
{
    static void Main(string[] args)
    {
        // Generate 10 random rows
        int rows = 10;

        // Generate and write the CSV file
        using (StreamWriter writer = new StreamWriter("output.csv"))
        {
            writer.WriteLine("First Column,Second Column");
            Random random = new Random();
            for (int i = 0; i < rows; i++)
            {
                int firstColumn = random.Next(1, 21);
                int secondColumn = random.Next(1, 101);
                writer.WriteLine($"{firstColumn},{secondColumn}");
            }
        }

        Console.WriteLine("CSV file generated successfully.");
    }
}
```

This code will generate a file called "output.csv" in the same directory as your C# file. Each row will be written in CSV format, with the values separated by a comma. The first row will contain the column headers.

After running this code, you can open the "output.csv" file with a spreadsheet software or a text editor, and you will see the values in the desired CSV format.

